<plot>The civil rights photographs taken by Southern Charles Moore are credited with helping to quicken the passage of the Civil Rights Act of 1964. The noted historian, Arthur Schlesinger, Jr. said that Moore's photographs transformed the national mood and made the legislation not just necessary, but possible. This is his story.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?100170</url></doc>
